                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.13/130a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-19T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 19, 1919—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5285. From Polk. Many thanks for your 3801. Notified French we were leaving Paris
                    4th or 5th of December. Will you be kind enough to arrange with War Department
                    to have <hi rend="italic">America</hi> sail December 6th? I will probably return
                    on <hi rend="italic">America</hi>. We are already in touch with General Connor
                    arranging for shipping personnel and files. Am leaving for London tomorrow and
                    will be back Tuesday. Looking forward to seeing you soon. Polk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
